<br>
I write this in haste...<br>
<br>
I have fallen prey to a new group of rogues in the mountainous region of the Western Plains of Karana.  I stumbled upon them by accident, only to have them slay me within seconds.  In truth at that time, I did not even have time to consider their strength.<br>
<br>
By the grace of the gods, I was recreated within the Greater Faydark Forest, where a kind wizard teleported me to the Northern Plains of Karana.  With cammoflage provided to me by a druid, I was able to steal close to their camp and retreive my corpse and its equipment.<br>
<br>
There appear to be four of these individuals and they are no mere bandits.  Each is named and most are slightly weaker than myself while one (a spellcaster) appears to be much stronger.  Their camp was situated NW of the Ogre Shrine in the mountains and just west of a camp of Karana Bandits.<br>
<br>
Beware as you travel through the mountains, for they are now infested with things far worse than the bandits which plague the region.<br>
